{"id":61837,"title":"Treatment of human papillomavirus infection with interferon alpha and ribavirin in a patient with acquired aplastic anemia.","abstract":"Genital warts caused by human papillomavirus (HPV) are the most frequent sexually transmitted infection. We describe a case of severe perianal and genital HPV infection in a patient with acquired aplastic anemia, unresponsive to traditional therapies and treated effectively with a combination of interferon and ribavirin. ","date":"2014-05-26","categories":"Hemic and Lymphatic Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24661930","annotations":[{"name":"Genital wart","weight":0.913439,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Genital_wart"},{"name":"Human papillomavirus","weight":0.910027,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_papillomavirus"},{"name":"Ribavirin","weight":0.906012,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ribavirin"},{"name":"Sexually transmitted disease","weight":0.891056,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sexually_transmitted_disease"},{"name":"Interferon","weight":0.808903,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interferon"},{"name":"Sex organ","weight":0.771398,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sex_organ"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.754651,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Anemia","weight":0.750864,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anemia"},{"name":"Wart","weight":0.744384,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wart"},{"name":"Infection","weight":0.72904,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infection"},{"name":"Anus","weight":0.70749,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anus"},{"name":"Human","weight":0.65762,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human"},{"name":"Interferon type I","weight":0.495147,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interferon_type_I"},{"name":"Aplastic anemia","